From the INITIAL LINE is associated an orthonormal reference system E0
defined by the 3 points P01 P02 P03 
.P01 is the origin
.P01-P02 define the first  vector E1
.P01-P03 define the second vector E2, thus
 E3 = E1 PRODUIT VECTORIEL E2
 E2 = E3 PRODUIT VECTORIEL E1
Norm(E1)=Norm(E2)=Norm(E3)=1

For every slice i, an orthonormal reference system Ei is defined
from the 3 points i, in a same way.

The MAPPING of the INITIAL LINE is the MAPPING of the DISPLACEMENT
from E0 to Ei

The vertices from 2 consecutive lines are joined to define quadrangles.

Example: S14.0; I; 14;INITIAL_ LINE; 0; 2; {number of slices}
         P01;P02;P03;  P11;P12;P13;   P21;P22;P23;
        {the 3 points i define the reference system Ei}
